    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section>
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>The following compounds involve bogsa with a post-specifier – <ul>
                    <li><g>bogsa nan <a href="?gd=litir">litrichean</a></g>
                        <en>postbox</en></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>


    <section>
        <h>uses</h>

        <section>
            <h>complement</h>
            <p><g>bogsa</g> can be the complement of certain prespoitions – <ul>
                    <li><g><a href="?gd=an^preposition">ann am</a> bogsa</g>
                        <en>in a box</en> – <ul>
                            <li><g><a href="?gd=tilg">tilg</a> ann am bogsa</g>
                                <en>throw something into a box</en> – <ul>
                                    <li>older pedagogical examples – <xl id="dep-comps-older-pedag">
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>Tha mo mhàthair a’ sgrìobhadh litreach gu
                                                  m’athair a tha air falbh. Thubhairt mo mhàthair,
                                                  “An téid thu do bhocsa nan litrichean leis an
                                                  litir seo, Iain?” “Théid,” ars Iain, “falbhaidh mi
                                                  an dràsda”. “Fuirich gus an dùin mi i is gus an
                                                  cuir mi seòladh oirre. Ceannaich fhéin stamp agus
                                                  cuir oirre i.” Tha Iain a’ ruith sìos an rathad
                                                  leis an litir ’na làimh. Théid e a steach do oifig
                                                  a’ phuist, ceannaichidh e stamp is cuiridh e sud
                                                  air an litir. <m>Tilgidh e an litir ann am bocsa
                                                  nan litrichean.</m>
                                                </gd>
                                                <tr>My mother is writing a letter to my father who
                                                  is away. My mother said, “Will you go to the
                                                  postbox with this letter, John?” “Yes, I will,”
                                                  said John, “I will leave now.” “Wait until I seal
                                                  it and put an address on it. Buy a stamp and put
                                                  it on it.” John is running down the road with the
                                                  letter in his hand. He will go into the post
                                                  office, he will buy a stamp and put that on the
                                                  letter. He will toss the letter into the
                                                  postbox.</tr>
                                                <ref text="621">td. 5</ref>
                                            </li>
                                        </xl></li>
